com.urbancode.ubuild.scripting.wrappers
Class ChangeSetWrapper

java.lang.Object
  com.urbancode.ubuild.scripting.wrappers.ChangeSetWrapper

public class ChangeSetWrapper
extends java.lang.Object

Scripting class to give limited access to ChangeSet information. This is exposed through methods on the buildLife object in notification scripts.

Examples:

To get the changes tied to a change set: 

    buildLife.getChangeSets().get(0).getChanges()
To get a comma-separated list of all of the change paths for a change set: 
    buildLife.getChangeSets().get(0).getChangePaths()
To get the issues tied to a change set: 
    buildLife.getChangeSets().get(0).getIssues()
To get the comment on a given change set: 
    buildLife.getChangeSets().get(0).getComment()
To get the date for a change set: 
    buildLife.getChangeSets().get(0).getDate()
To get the change id for a change set: 
    buildLife.getChangeSets().get(0).getId()
To get the properties tied to a change set: 
    buildLife.getChangeSets().get(0).getProperties()
To get the name of the source config used for a change set: 
    buildLife.getChangeSets().get(0).getSourceConfig()
To get the time for a change set: 
    buildLife.getChangeSets().get(0).getTime()
To get the name of the user for the change set: 
    buildLife.getChangeSets().get(0).getUser()
If you are using velocity scripts for Notification Templates, you don't have to use the full method name for getters: 
    buildLife.getChangeSets().get(0).Changes
    buildLife.getChangeSets().get(0).ChangePaths
    buildLife.getChangeSets().get(0).Issues
    buildLife.getChangeSets().get(0).Comment
    buildLife.getChangeSets().get(0).Date
    buildLife.getChangeSets().get(0).Id
    buildLife.getChangeSets().get(0).Properties
    buildLife.getChangeSets().get(0).SourceConfig
    buildLife.getChangeSets().get(0).Time
    buildLife.getChangeSets().get(0).User
